  "body": "**üìù Details**\r\nThe functions `getProxyImplementation()` and `getProxyAdmin()` found in the contracts/proxy/transparent/ProxyAdmin.sol contract can be improved, in particular, before calling `abi.decode(returndata, (address))`, the `require(success)` checks could be changed into `require(success && returndata.length == 32)`.\r\n\r\nFindings:\r\n - https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/proxy/transparent/ProxyAdmin.sol#L26\r\n - https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/proxy/transparent/ProxyAdmin.sol#L41\r\n\r\nPoC: https://gist.github.com/tin-z/143462696c43d26fc301675ed38c9a40\r\n\r\n\r\n**üßê Motivation**\r\nI reported this as  a revert causing DoS vulnerability but it seems that the revert exception was already expected.",
